children.text: There has not been a balustrade fitted to the retaining wall along the path of access to the building in this area to protect the occupants from falls.
Part 3.9.2.2 Barriers to prevent falls of the NCC’s Building Code of Australia (BCA) requires that
‘A continuous barrier must be provided along the side of a trafficable surface, such as a
retaining wall that forms part of, or is directly associated with a delineated path of access to a building from the road, or a delineated path of access between buildings (see Figure 3.9.2.2)’ ;
A balustrade must be immediately installed to this area in accordance with the requirements of the BCA.
